Mobile Optimization Plan — Corsair Catch
Context
The game is currently desktop-only (WASD keyboard input, 1280x720 hardcoded positions, no touch support). It's completely unplayable on phones/tablets. The CLAUDE.md already lists mobile optimization as a next priority. This plan makes the game fully playable on mobile while preserving the existing desktop experience.

Key design decisions:

Force landscape (not portrait) — the entire game world, all NPC/item positions, dock zones, and walk bounds are calibrated to 16:9. Portrait would require a complete redesign.
Phaser-native joystick (not HTML overlay, not nipple.js) — keeps everything inside the canvas, auto-scales with FIT mode, no DOM/canvas z-index coordination needed.
Floating joystick pattern — joystick appears where you touch (left 40% of screen), more natural than a fixed position.
Context-sensitive action buttons — instead of mapping all 6+ keyboard shortcuts, show only the 2-3 actions relevant to current game state.
