Phase 1: MVP — Game Playable on Mobile (~1 session)
Step 1: Create src/systems/MobileInput.ts (NEW FILE)
Core mobile input system. ~200-250 lines. Contains:

IS_MOBILE static flag — 'ontouchstart' in window || navigator.maxTouchPoints > 0
Virtual joystick — Phaser Container on a UI camera (fixed to screen, not world)
Base circle: semi-transparent, 120px diameter
Thumb circle: 40px, tracks pointer within 50px max radius
Floating pattern: appears at touch position in left 40% of screen
Returns normalized movement vector { x: -1..1, y: -1..1 }
Action button — 80px gold circle at bottom-right
Acts as SPACE equivalent (interact, confirm, reel fish)
Contextual label changes per game state
Multi-touch pointer separation — left 40% = joystick, right 40% = action, tracked by pointer ID
Public API:
getMovementVector(): { x: number, y: number }
isActionJustDown(): boolean
showContextButtons(context: 'overworld' | 'battle' | 'sailing')
destroy()
